==背景==
{{see|Wikipedia:頁面存廢討論}}
由於擔心破壞性和不恰當的內容，大部份[[Wiki|Wiki]]需要有關內容收錄的政策。<ref name="Bryan">Lowell Bryan, Mobilizing Minds: Creating Wealth from Talent in the 21st Century Organization, p. 223, McGraw-Hill (2007), ISBN 978-0-07-149082-5</ref>維基百科已經發展政策解決與個別條目有關的糾紛。<ref name="Benkler">Yochai Benkler, The Wealth of Networks, p. 73, Yale University Press (2006), ISBN 978-0-300-12577-1</ref>這些討論在「頁面存廢討論」頁進行，只要是自動確認用戶或條目作者都可以發起。<ref name="Segal">{{cite news
| url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/12/02/AR2006120201111_pf.html
| title = Look Me Up Under 'Missing Link': On Wikipedia, Oblivion Looms for the Non-Notable
| author = David Segal
| work = [[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]
| date = 2006-12-03
| accessdate = 2008-01-23
| archive-date = 2008-10-16
| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081016140408/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/12/02/AR2006120201111_pf.html
| dead-url = no
}}</ref>很多討論關注的不僅是每篇條目的內容，而且還有「對如何編輯一個理想的百科全書的不同觀點」。<ref name="Rettberg">{{cite web| url = http://www.retts.net/documents/cnarrativeDAC.pdf| title = All Together Now: Collective Knowledge, Collective Narratives, and Architectures of Participation| author = Scott Rettberg of The Richard Stockton College of New Jersey| page = 8| format = PDF| publisher = Digital Arts and Culture Conference Proceedings| year = 2005| accessdate = 2008-01-24| archive-date = 2008-01-21| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080121183703/http://retts.net/documents/cnarrativeDAC.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref>

每次討論結束後，管理員會判定和執行社羣共識。不需要討論的條目（如明顯的廣告頁面）可以被標記並由管理員刪除而不須經討論。<ref name="sym">{{cite web
